metadata.name: Plottable Wireframe (8 frames) #30
metadata.description:
More info: https://greweb.me/plots/509

'Wireframe' explores the realm of 3D noise mixed with various generative techniques. Many rare features and easter eggs are to discover.

A SVG file can be exported (right click save) to plot the 8 frames of this animation on a A4 paper. This collection is the first "plot loop" generator on a NFT marketplace.

You can enjoy the digital version that simulate ink effects and optional, thanks to the utility token decoupling, get a physical one: the digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece, owning it confers the right to plot or request a physical plot from @greweb (https://greweb.me/plots/nft). @greweb would use fountain pens but other plotting artists are free to achieve it with their own materials and ship to collectors – as long as NFT is owned at request time.

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: Points of origin #2
metadata.description:
Points of origin is an interactive audio-visual artwork made of generative point-cloud patterns.
This piece touches on the problem of universals by visualizing the relationships between particles and forms.

Live controls

Rotation - Click and drag or tap and drag
Zoom - Mouse wheel or pinch
Scroll (pinch on mobile) - Zoom
Double click (double tap on mobile) - Restart the camera
1,2,3 - Particle density (low, medium, and high) 
1 - Low, approx. 500000 particles
2 - Medium (default), approx. 1000000 particles
3 - High, approx. 2000000 particles
S - Save PNG screenshot (the size depends on the resolution)
M - Toggle sound (mute / unmute)

Use full-screen mode for the best experience.

Adi Dizdarevic, 2022
Made with the Cables.gl, custom Eurorack modular, and VA audio production tools.

metadata.name: Star polygon II #26
metadata.description:
Celebrating the beauty of Mathematics with a second project about star polygons.

--------

"A star polygon {p/q}, with p,q positive integers, is a figure formed by connecting with straight lines every qth point out of p regularly spaced points lying on a circumference." 
(Wolfram MathWorld)

--------

There are 6 palettes, 9 polygons, 6 icons.

"S" to save 2000x2000 png.

Created by Carla Chicchiero in p5.js

metadata.name: Artifice #339
metadata.description:
This series is is about playful obfuscation.

The fxtext article linked on the main profect goes more in-depth into what is meant by that, as well as the events that led to this collection.

5640 bytes of Vanilla JS with no libraries. Palettes make up a third of the code.

In live mode:
‘S’ : save as png (3000 × 3600)
’V’ : save as svg (without grain)

URL params in live mode:
‘g=n’ : no grain
‘g=p’ : paper grain
‘h=t’ : high resolution mode, 9000 ×10600 (Chrome only, and may take a moment)

For example, if you wanted paper grain in high resolution, append “&g=p&h=t” to the url in live mode.

After rendering with these params, tapping 'P' will then save a png with those settings applied.
